posts.title: Trump's security needs to be beefed up ten trillion percent.
posts.content:
The kind of stuff Trump is talking about doing is fantastic -- it's the kind of stuff that needs to be done to save the nation. But he probably has enemies plotting against him who would be happy to spend billions of dollars to eliminate him and his team.

I don't know what if anything we can do to pump up his security at least until the inauguration, but if there's anything, we should do it. There's hardly any amount of security that would be too much in a situation like this.

Powell didn’t mention, however, that The Federal Reserve is unconstitutional to…

twitter.content:
The President can suspend the Fed Chairman's security clearance. 

Courts cannot review the President's decisions on security clearances.

Without a security clearance, the Fed Chairman cannot really do anything at all. He would have no choice but to resign.
